[{"id":"VR731851","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">In plants the enzyme <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E P S P\"><math alttext=\"E P S P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>EPSP</mi></math></span></span> synthase catalyzes a reaction between two different substrates, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S 3 P\"><math alttext=\"S 3 P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P E P\"><math alttext=\"P E P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PEP</mi></math></span></span>, to form a product used in the synthesis of three amino acids. The structure of glyphosate, the active chemical in many herbicides, is very similar to that of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P E P\"><math alttext=\"P E P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PEP</mi></math></span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following explains how glyphosate most likely functions as an herbicide?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR731851_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Glyphosate prevents synthesis of the three amino acids by competing with <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P E P\"><math alttext=\"P E P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PEP</mi></math></span></span> for binding to the active site of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E P S P\"><math alttext=\"E P S P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>EPSP</mi></math></span></span> synthase.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Glyphosate prevents synthesis of the three amino acids by binding to an allosteric site of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E P S P\"><math alttext=\"E P S P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>EPSP</mi></math></span></span> synthase, increasing the likelihood that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P E P\"><math alttext=\"P E P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PEP</mi></math></span></span> will bind to the active site.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Glyphosate causes too much synthesis of the three amino acids by reducing the activation energy of the reaction catalyzed by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E P S P\"><math alttext=\"E P S P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>EPSP</mi></math></span></span> synthase.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Glyphosate alters the structure of the three amino acids by binding to both <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S 3 P\"><math alttext=\"S 3 P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P E P\"><math alttext=\"P E P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PEP</mi></math></span></span> in the active site of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E P S P\"><math alttext=\"E P S P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>EPSP</mi></math></span></span> synthase.</p>"],"answer":0}]